name: TestReport
title: TestReport
description: A summary of information based on the results of executing a TestScript.

elements.name: TestReport
elements.description: A summary of information based on the results of executing a TestScript.

elements.name: identifier
elements.description: Identifier for the TestScript assigned for external purposes outside the context of FHIR.

elements.name: name
elements.description: A free text natural language name identifying the executed TestScript.

elements.name: status
elements.description: The current state of this test report.

elements.name: testScript
elements.description: Ideally this is an absolute URL that is used to identify the version-specific TestScript that was executed, matching the TestScript.url.

elements.name: result
elements.description: The overall result from the execution of the TestScript.

elements.name: score
elements.description: The final score (percentage of tests passed) resulting from the execution of the TestScript.

elements.name: tester
elements.description: Name of the tester producing this report (Organization or individual).

elements.name: issued
elements.description: When the TestScript was executed and this TestReport was generated.

elements.name: participant
elements.description: A participant in the test execution, either the execution engine, a client, or a server.

elements.name: setup
elements.description: The results of the series of required setup operations before the tests were executed.

elements.name: test
elements.description: A test executed from the test script.

elements.name: teardown
elements.description: The results of the series of operations required to clean up after all the tests were executed.
